    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive configuration for May 1st highlights a massive leverage opportunity against Christian Scott, whose 15.44 xERA makes **Josh Lowe** (72.21) and **Nolan Schanuel** (64.63) high-upside plays. The crown jewel of the lineup today is **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (75.66), who draws a favorable matchup against Simeon Woods Richardson; his elite xwOBA of 0.389 and the +19% boost from the pitcher\u2019s projected volatility solidify his role as the anchor. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** (75.34) remains an automatic start; he benefits from a +10% boost due to his lead-off spot, and while Will Warren presents a moderate challenge, **Henderson**\u2019s current plate discipline profile maintains his status as our primary engine for Runs and SB opportunities.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved leaving **Marcell Ozuna** (59.72) on the bench. Despite a favorable wind-out condition and a +7% boost from the opposing SP skill set, **Ozuna** fell just short of the 60.00 threshold required to displace lower-floor starters like **Dominic Smith**. The optimizer prioritized the categorical scarcity of SB production; even though **Ozuna** offers superior raw power, the decision to slot in **Heliot Ramos** (60.35) and **Dominic Smith** (55.61) was driven by a commitment to maintaining a baseline efficiency across all five categories. **Jackson Merrill** (53.92) was also considered, but his -13% platoon penalty against Noah Schultz made him an easy exclusion in a day where maximizing efficiency per game cap is paramount.\n\nRisks remain, as the majority of these scores are tethered to pending lineups; should **Drake Baldwin** (72.68) or **Miguel Vargas** (61.94) move down in their respective batting orders, their efficiency scores will adjust downward significantly. We are also closely monitoring the slow delivery rates of the opposing pitchers facing **Miguel Vargas** and **Heliot Ramos**, which provide a subtle but meaningful +2% boost to their SB projections. While the matchup against Jose Quintana looks favorable for **Drake Baldwin**, we are treating these projections with caution until the final confirmed lineups are verified, particularly given the volatility inherent in our current OF depth.",
